9 An Act relating to driver licenses; requiring Service
Oklahoma to enact certain license tracking system by
10 or before certain date; requiring Service Oklahoma to
enact certain expedited delivery of credentials by or
11 before certain date; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
12 emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-101.6 of Title 47, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. By or before January 1, 2027, Service Oklahoma shall enact a
20 system that enables an individual to track the mailing status of a
21 driver license or identification card issued to such individual by
22 Service Oklahoma. Such system shall consist of an update via
23 electronic communication sent directly to an individual about a
24 change in the mailing status of a driver license or identification
SB1221 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 card or a web portal where an individual may register to view the
2 current mailing status of a driver license.
3 B. By or before January 1, 2027, Service Oklahoma shall enact a
4 system that enables an applicant for a credential to be issued by
5 Service Oklahoma, including REAL ID Compliant and REAL ID
6 Noncompliant driver licenses and identification cards, to request
7 expedited delivery of the credential at the time of issuance. For
8 those electing for expedited delivery, there shall be assessed, in
9 addition to any other fees provided for by law, an expedited
10 delivery fee of Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00). The expedited
11 delivery fee shall be deposited to the credit of the Service
12 Oklahoma Revolving Fund.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
14 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
15 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
16 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
17 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
18
